General
~~~~~~~

* Requirments:
	- C++ compiler
	- CMake >= 2.6
	- wxWidgets >= 2.8
	  modules: core

* Compiling
	- Make a build directory
	- Use CMake to generate makefiles for your OS
	- Compile those makefiles using the correct compiler


Ubuntu
~~~~~~

* Requirments
	- C++ compiler
	  sudo aptitude install build-essential
	- CMake >= 2.6
	  sudo aptitude install cmake
	- wxWidgets >= 2.8
	  sudo aptitude install ...


Windows
~~~~~~~

* Requirments:
	- Visual C++ 2008 Express Edition (free)
	   http://www.microsoft.com/express/vc/
	- CMake >= 2.6
	   http://www.cmake.org/cmake/resources/software.html
	- wxWidgets >= 2.8
	   http://www.wxwidgets.org/downloads/

* Compiling wxWidgets
	- Extract the archive you downloaded somewhere
	- set WXWIN="path to your wxWidgets sources" (e.g. set WXWIN="c:\wxWidgets")
	- cd %WXWIN%\build\msw 
	- nmake -f makefile.vc 

* Compiling
	- Make a subdirectory "build", and enter it
	- Use CMake to generate a set of makefiles
	  cmake ..\ -G "Visual Studio 9 2008"
	- Open "Inkpad.sln"
	- Hit "Build"